<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="bitter-adj">bitter <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'bɪtə(r)/    美 /'bɪtər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(味道) 苦的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Good medicine is bitter in the mouth. 
良药苦口。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>㊔ The roots of education are bitter, but the fruit is sweet.
教育的根是苦涩的，但其果实是香甜的。</p><footer>——亚里士多德</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>[只用于名词前] 辛酸的；痛苦的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>bitter tears</strong> 
辛酸的眼泪</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a bitter experience 
痛苦的经历</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>充满仇恨 (怨恨) 的</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>was bitter about</strong> losing the job. 
他丢掉了工作，心里愤愤不平。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>bitterly  /'bɪtərli/ adv   </p></div>